    <description>Now that we’ve seen how merge sort works by going through an example, let’s look at the pseudocode of a merge sort function.&#xA;1function MERGESORT(ARRAY, START, END) 2 # base case size == 1 3 if END - START + 1 == 1 then 4 return 5 end if 6 # base case size == 2 7 if END - START + 1 == 2 then 8 # check if elements are out of order 9 if ARRAY[START] &gt; ARRAY[END] then 10 # swap if so 11 TEMP = ARRAY[START] 12 ARRAY[START] = ARRAY[END] 13 ARRAY[END] = TEMP 14 end if 15 return 16 end if 17 # find midpoint 18 HALF = int((START + END) / 2) 19 # sort first half 20 MERGESORT(ARRAY, START, HALF) 21 # sort second half 22 MERGESORT(ARRAY, HALF + 1, END) 23 # merge halves 24 MERGE(ARRAY, START, HALF, END) 25end function This function is a recursive function which has two base cases.</description>
